5000|$|In {{television}} <b>broadcast</b> <b>camera</b> work, {{the amount}} of headroom seen by the production crew is slightly greater than the amount seen by home viewers, whose frames are reduced in area by about 5%. To adjust for this, <b>broadcast</b> <b>camera</b> headroom is slightly expanded so that home viewers will see the correct amount of headroom. Professional video camera viewfinders and professional video monitors often include an overscan setting to compare between full screen resolution and [...] "domestic cut-off" [...] {{as an aid to}} achieving good headroom and lead room.|$|E
