50|$|Plumbicon is a {{registered}} trademark of Philips for its Lead(II) oxide (PbO) target vidicons. Used frequently in <b>broadcast</b> <b>camera</b> applications, these tubes have low output, but a high signal-to-noise ratio. They had excellent resolution compared to Image Orthicons, but lacked the artificially sharp edges of IO tubes, which caused some of the viewing audience to perceive them as softer. CBS Labs invented the first outboard edge enhancement circuits to sharpen the edges of Plumbicon generated images.|$|E
